KINGAN & CO. INCORPORATED v. Will H. SMITH, etc. No. 6118. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit Feb. 15, 1937. Val Nolan, of Indianapolis, Ind., for appellant. William H. Thompson, Albert L. Rabb, and Thomas D. Stevenson, of Indianapolis, Ind., for appellee.

Before EVANS „ and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered by the court that leave be denied to the G. M. Peet Packing Company to file a brief as amicus curiae.
